 |\n\n**Total: 22 page files**\n\n---\n\n## 2. Service Files (`app/services/`)\n\n### API Service Layer (`app/services/api/`)\n| File | Absolute Path |\n|------|--------------|\n| `api/authService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/authService.ts` |\n| `api/propertyService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/propertyService.ts` |\n| `api/inquiryService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/inquiryService.ts` |\n| `api/favoriteService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/favoriteService.ts` |\n| `api/profileService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/profileService.ts` |\n| `api/adminService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/adminService.ts` |\n| `api/amenityService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/api/amenityService.ts` |\n\n### HTTP Transport Layer (`app/services/`)\n| File | Absolute Path |\n|------|--------------|\n| `httpService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/httpService.ts` |\n| `httpServices/userService.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/services/httpServices/userService.ts` |\n\n**Total: 9 service files**\n\n---\n\n## 3. Hook Files (`app/hooks/`)\n\n### API Hooks (TanStack Query wrappers — `app/hooks/api/`)\n| File | Absolute Path |\n|------|--------------|\n| `api/useAuth.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useAuth.ts` |\n| `api/useProperties.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useProperties.ts` |\n| `api/useInquiries.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useInquiries.ts` |\n| `api/useFavorites.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useFavorites.ts` |\n| `api/useProfile.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useProfile.ts` |\n| `api/useAdmin.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useAdmin.ts` |\n| `api/useAmenities.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/api/useAmenities.ts` |\n\n### Provider & Auth Hook (`app/hooks/`)\n| File | Absolute Path |\n|------|--------------|\n| `useAuth.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/useAuth.ts` |\n| `providers/providers.tsx` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/hooks/providers/providers.tsx` |\n\n**Total: 9 hook files**\n\n---\n\n## 4. package.json — Dependencies\n\n### Runtime Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `@hookform/resolvers` | ^5.2.2 | Zod integration for React Hook Form |\n| `@radix-ui/react-label` | ^2.1.8 | Accessible label primitives |\n| `@radix-ui/react-slot` | ^1.2.4 | Slot composition |\n| `@react-router/node` | ^7.15.1 | React Router 7 server/node utilities |\n| **`@reduxjs/toolkit`** | **^2.12.0** | **Redux state management** |\n| **`@tanstack/react-query`** | **^5.36.0** | **Server-state / data fetching** |\n| **`axios`** | **^1.7.0** | **HTTP client** |\n| `class-variance-authority` | ^0.7.1 | Component variant management |\n| `clsx` | ^2.1.1 | Conditional className utility |\n| `i18next` | ^26.2.0 | Internationalization |\n| `i18next-browser-languagedetector` | ^8.2.1 | Auto language detection |\n| `i18next-http-backend` | ^4.0.0 | Lazy-load locale files |\n| `isbot` | ^5 | Bot detection |\n| `lucide-react` | ^1.16.0 | Icon library |\n| `react` | ^18.3.1 | React |\n| `react-dom` | ^18.3.1 | React DOM |\n| `react-hook-form` | ^7.76.0 | Form state management |\n| `react-i18next` | ^17.0.8 | React i18n bindings |\n| `react-redux` | ^9.3.0 | React Redux bindings |\n| `react-router-dom` | ^6.30.3 | Client-side routing |\n| `tailwind-merge` | ^3.6.0 | Tailwind class merging |\n| `zod` | ^4.4.3 | Schema validation |\n\n### Key Observations\n- **Both `@reduxjs/toolkit` AND `@tanstack/react-query` are present** — this is a dual-pattern architecture.\n- **`react-router-dom` ^6.30.3** is installed (not `react-router` directly), alongside `@react-router/node` ^7.15.1.\n- Standard form stack: `react-hook-form` + `zod` + `@hookform/resolvers`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Redux Store Files\n\n| File | Absolute Path |\n|------|--------------|\n| `store/store.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/redux/store/store.ts` |\n| `store/rootReducer.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/redux/store/rootReducer.ts` |\n| `store/hooks.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/redux/store/hooks.ts` |\n| `features/authSlice.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/redux/features/authSlice.ts` |\n| `features/userSlice.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/frontend/app/redux/features/userSlice.ts` |\n\n**Store structure:**\n- Uses `configureStore` from Redux Toolkit.\n- Two slices: `auth` and `user`.\n- `authSlice` manages `user`, `isAuthenticated`, `isLoading`, `authChecked`, `error` and has four async thunks (`loginUser`, `registerUser`, `fetchCurrentUser`, `logoutUser`).\n- `userSlice` consumes `createAsyncThunk` imports from `httpServices/userService.ts` (`fetchUsers`, `createUser`).\n- Typed hooks exported: `useAppDispatch` / `useAppSelector`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. API Integration Patterns\n\nThere are **two side-by-side API integration patterns** in this codebase:\n\n### Pattern A: TanStack React Query (primary pattern used by pages)\n\n**Flow: `Service Layer` → `Hook` → `Component`**\n\n1. **Service files** (`app/services/api/*.ts`) — Plain async functions wrapping `httpService`:\n   ```ts\n   // app/services/api/authService.ts\n   export const authService = {\n     login: (data: LoginDto) => httpService.post<LoginResponse>('/auth/login', data),\n     getMe: () => httpService.get<AuthUser>('/auth/me'),\n   };\n   ```\n   Every API service file imports from `~/services/httpService`.\n\n2. **Hook files** (`app/hooks/api/*.ts`) — TanStack Query `useQuery` / `useMutation` wrappers:\n   ```ts\n   // app/hooks/api/useAuth.ts\n   export function useLogin() {\n     const queryClient = useQueryClient();\n     return useMutation({\n       mutationFn: (data: LoginDto) => authService.login(data),\n       onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['auth', 'me'] }),\n     });\n   }\n   ```\n   - Queries use structured keys like `['properties', 'search', params]`, `['admin', 'dashboard']`, `['favorites', params]`.\n   - Mutations call `queryClient.invalidateQueries()` on success to refresh related data.\n   - `enabled: !!id` pattern used for id-dependent queries.\n\n3. **Pages** call hooks directly:\n   ```ts\n   // app/pages/auth/login.tsx\n   const login = useLogin();\n   // ...\n   login.mutate(data);\n   ```\n\n### Pattern B: Redux Async Thunks (less common, used for auth/user)\n\n**Flow: `createAsyncThunk` → `Slice extraReducers` → `Component via dispatch`**\n\n1. **Thunks defined in service files** (`app/services/httpServices/userService.ts`) or slice files:\n   ```ts\n   export const fetchUsers = createAsyncThunk(\n     'user/fetchUsers',\n     async (_, { rejectWithValue }) => {\n       try {\n         return await userService.getUsers();\n       } catch (error: any) {\n         return rejectWithValue(error.message);\n       }\n     }\n   );\n   ```\n\n2. **Slices** handle `pending`/`fulfilled`/`rejected` states:\n   ```ts\n   // app/redux/features/authSlice.ts\n   .addCase(loginUser.pending, (state) => { state.isLoading = true; })\n   .addCase(loginUser.fulfilled, (state, action) => { state.user = action.payload; })\n   ```\n\n3. **Auth initialization** runs via `dispatch(fetchCurrentUser())` in `Providers` component on mount.\n\n### The HTTP Transport Core (`httpService.ts`)\n\n- Axios instance with `withCredentials: true` (cookie-based auth).\n- Response interceptor for automatic 401 → token refresh → retry.\n- All methods (`get`, `post`, `put`, `patch`, `delete`) unwrap `ApiResponse<T>` to return just `T`.\n- Base URL from `VITE_API_URL` env var or falls back to `http://localhost:3000/api`.\n\n### Provider Hierarchy (from `providers.tsx`)\n\n```\nQueryClientProvider (TanStack Query)\n  └── Provider (Redux)\n        └── AuthInitializer (dispatches fetchCurrentUser on mount)\n              └── children (the app)\n```\n\n### Summary Table of the Dual Pattern\n\n| Concern | TanStack Query | Redux |\n|---------|---------------|-------|\n| Server-state (properties, inquiries, favorites, profile, amenities, admin stats) | `useQuery` / `useMutation` hooks in `app/hooks/api/` | Not used |\n| Auth session (login/register/me/logout) | `useLogin`, `useRegister`, etc. in `useAuth.ts` hooks | `authSlice` with `loginUser`, `fetchCurrentUser` thunks |\n| Generic CRUD (users) | Not used | `userSlice` with `fetchUsers`, `createUser` thunks |\n| Auth state (isAuthenticated, user) | Not used | `authSlice` (read by `useAuth` hook via Redux selector) |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1bc4b4b8cffe0nK0wwHHNx2kzK","sessionId":"ses_1bc4b05c3ffeIfQf3NXQq7HRUb","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore frontend structure","time":{"start":1779252394559,"end":1779252588645}},"id":"prt_e43b4e2870016matki8I5cALy9","sessionID":"ses_1bc4b4b8cffe0nK0wwHHNx2kzK","messageID":"msg_e43b4b811001nF9gETmgR6ACyA"}}
